# Github poorly handles LFS memory management: the only way to free space is to delete entire repo. Source on November 2022: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/working-with-files/managing-large-files/removing-files-from-git-large-file-storage#git-lfs-objects-in-your-repository
# Another useful link: https://gregoryszorc.com/blog/2021/05/12/why-you-shouldn%27t-use-git-lfs/
# Because of this, I decided not to include LFS management to the template. 
# Instead, for each new project an explicit decision should be made on whether or not to include LFS support.
# In case one decided to include it, below is the template for LFS support:
# Image formats
    #*.psd filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.jpg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.gif filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.bmp filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.tga filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.tiff filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.tif filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.iff filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.pict filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.dds filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
    #*.xcf filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
